==Old English==

===Etymology===
From West Germanic ''*faka-'', cognate with Latin [[pangere]].  Germanic cognates include Old High German [[fah]] (German [[Fach]]), Old Saxon [[fak]] (Dutch [[vak]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /fæk/

===Noun===
'''fæc''' ''n'' (''pl'' '''facu''')
# an [[interval]], a period of time

